data.description: Family-oriented community houses this 4-bedroom/2.5-bath home. The original owner wants to invite the next family to enjoy what he has carefully cared for over the past 8 years. The owner's suite is oversized and has vaulted ceilings with enough space to accommodate all the pieces of a California king-size bedroom set. Separate soaking tub from the shower and separated vanities. There's a walk-in closet in this massive bedroom. The other 3 bedrooms are spacious enough to hold king-sized beds in each room. The laundry room is conveniently located upstairs near the bedrooms. Downstairs is a 2-story foyer that opens to the main level. There are 2 separated coat closets and a powder room for guests. The formal living room has bay windows and shares the same side of the house with the formal dining room, which seats 12 easily. The kitchen is a chef's dream. Double built-in ovens, gas stove top, 42' upper cabinets, functional island in the center, pantry, granite countertops, and built-in microwave. The double sink is nestled in an additional granite countertop that overhangs into the family room. The eat-in kitchen can hold a 6-piece table set and overlooks the fenced-in private backyard. The coffered ceiling family room has a stone fireplace and provides accessibility to the covered patio out back. The shed is in place in the backyard for all the outside storage, so you won't have to use the 2-car garage space. Located 1/2 mile from 75 South, there are restaurants, a movie theater, fitness centers, Home Depot, Sam's Club, and a ton of other stores for shopping. House is being SOLD AS-IS. Priced to sell.
